 LINUS CHIBUIKE PRESIDENT Muhammadu Buhari and Vice President Yemi Osinbajo have received their COVID-19 vaccines at the Old Banquet Hall of the State House, Abuja. The President’s Chief Personal Physician, Dr Shuaib Rafindadi Sanusi, injected him with the vaccine, while the Vice President was injected by Dr Nicholas Odifre, his Personal Physician. Secretary to the Government of the Federation, Boss Mustapha; Minister of Health, Osagie Ehanire; Minister of Information and Culture, Lai Mohammed; and Chief of Staff to the President, Ibrahim Gambari, were present at the brief ceremony. Details later… 